==English==
===Adjective===
'''Concise'''
#expressing much with little to no [[extraneous]] [[detail]] or [[word]]s; not [[verbose]]; brief and precise.

===Etymology===
From Late Latin '''concisus''' ("cut short") < Latin ''concidere'' ("cut to pieces") < Latin ''[[caedere]]'' ("to cut, to strike down").

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/kən'saɪs/}}

